    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of Larix decidua, found from Bavaria to the Swiss Alps. Heartwood ranges in color from reddish brown to brick-red in color, and the timber is used for posts, poles, and boat planks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
